As Nigeria continues to battle the spread of Coronavirus, the Mountain of Fire and Miracles Ministries (MFM), has joined the likes of the Redeemed Christian Church of God (RCCG) in shutting down its parishes in Lagos and Ogun States. Following increase number of cases of Coronavirus in the Lagos, the state government had suspended social and religious gatherings of over 50 persons. Pastor Enoch Adeboye, General Overseer of RCCG had instructed its members to suspend services and obey the instructions of Ogun and Lagos governments to prevent the spread of the Coronavirus disease (COVID-19). Also, MFM Assistant General Overseer (Administration) Pastor Gbesan Adebambo in memo entitled: “Interim arrangement for ministerial services in Lagos and Ogun states MFM Regions” on Friday, ordered its parishes in Lagos and Oguns States to cancel all services The church also directed that all house fellowship meetings at any of the centres be postponed till further notice. The memo read: “No services including deliverance ministrations must hold in any of MFM branches at all levels in the Region under your supervision until further notice. “Likewise, all house fellowship meetings at any of the centres are postponed till further notice.”